1) JavaScript Changes on Website A/B Testing Tools
First, letâ€™s learn about DOM manipulation. Document Object Model manipulation or DOM manipulation is what Iâ€™d define as â€œchange a web page real-time just by using a web browser.â€

Websites are rendered by the browser. Whenever you see web pages, they are renditions of HTML, CSS and JavaScript code interpreted by the browser with an object element hierarchy. This is the DOM.

This means that if you can change these HTML elements within the web browser, you can change web pages in real-time. No need to go to the backend.

This is one of the basics of web development. I wonâ€™t bore anyone with the details. Just see for yourselfâ€¦

Do these steps:

Go to any web page
Press right-click
Click â€˜Inspectâ€™
You will now see something like this:

homepagescreen
This is the developer tool of Google Chrome called Chrome DevTools and this is whatâ€™s happening under the hood. The magic happens here!

I can now change elements on my homepage by traversing the DOM and whipping out a JavaScript code in the Console.

homepage 01
I was able to change the background color of my homepage without logging in WordPress. How cool is that!

Letâ€™s say you want to re-arrange an entire block or section of a web page. Thatâ€™s also possible.

homepage 02
I was able to re-arrange HTML elements on my website through Google Chrome by using the code below.

var header = document.querySelector('.elementor-section-wrap')
var intro = document.querySelector('.elementor-element-5c31627')
var services = document.querySelector('.elementor-element-0aa0836')
header.insertBefore(services, intro)
Anyone can try this so I encourage anyone to do this on my homepage! ðŸ˜‚

What does this have anything to do with digital marketing?

If someone works in digital marketing, specifically conversion rate optimization, the value of learning JavaScript comes from A/B testing pages. Conversion optimizers might rely on the visual editor that is built-in to these tools, but itâ€™s limited and it couldnâ€™t do a more granular change.

So, what to do? Make JavaScript changes.

Hereâ€™s an example of implementing JavaScript changes on Google Optimize (an A/B testing tool). Digital marketers or conversion optimizers will now able to make the changes themselves without waiting on web developers. Just find the Run JavaScript and put the code in.

GO
Google Optimize interface
Learning and practicing DOM manipulation in JavaScript will give more control over what to be A/B tested. Even though digital marketers canâ€™t do everything themselves, this hands-on practice can make digital marketers be more collaborative with web developers.

Web developers wonâ€™t be replaced. Web developers and designers are still needed if the changes on a page are too granular like a complete redesign. This part shows that certain changes (like remove elements or change the font size) can be done without pulling anyone.

